reviews.reviewText: This power supply worked perfect. Not only is my computer up and running again, but it no longer makes a high pitch noise whenever the mouse moves like it used to. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars OK for Power, Lousy FAN
reviews.reviewText: Installation was straightforward. Noticed right away the fan is loud. Not motor noise but the air noise sort of like a vacuum cleaner. After just over one year in service the internal fan quit completely making screeching bearing noises. I had a spare fan on hand and had to replace the original.Supply is now back to operation and MUCH quieter with a quality fan. Disassembling the old fan I found it was really cheap, only a four pole motor and cheap bearings.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 17, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Extremely noisy PSU from an Electromagnetic Interference (EMI) perspective
reviews.reviewText: I work with LF and VLF radio receivers and although that part of the spectrum is already crowded with spurious products from other cheap consumer electronics in a suburban environment, this PSU contributes very high-level spurious products from 200 kHz on up. The spurious signatures only change in frequency between PC ON, Standby, and OFF. The only way to get rid of them is to unplug the PC. My original Dell PSU was very EMI quiet, as most other high-quality switching supplies. My guess is that the primary and secondaries of this unit do not have adequate EMI filtering.

reviews.reviewTitle: It is important to know the matching of the item
reviews.reviewText: I liked the good character of the seller.
The power supply fit the computer fine but the fan (after 3 months started making a noise. Now the fan has quit. Not impressed.
